<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-08-01T11:41:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-08-01T11:41:00-05:00" n="1551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1551">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.404/2.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Vice Consul <persName type="from">Silliman</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Saltillo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-08-01T10:00:00-06:41">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 1, 1914—10 a.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Referring to previous correspondence regarding Church question.
                                Governor of Nuevo Leon said to me yesterday that his decree was a
                                revolutionary measure necessitated by the present exigencies of the
                                case and that when normal conditions again prevail the decree will
                                be subject to the action of the State legislature. The Governor of
                                Tamaulipas told me yesterday that he had not closed a single
                                Catholic church in the State but that he had expelled every Catholic
                                priest from the State.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>